I'm trying to go there again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look so good right now, but it's still Monday.
It's already clear where the problems lie. It's probably going to BE VERY difficult to get the medical authorization, due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will BE VERY time-consuming and means A LOT of extra work.
It's somewhat discouraging, but it's just another problem that needs to be solved. So far, it seems solvable. It just costs a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what's coming my way.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't give you medical authorization if you're taking medications for it.
